# Panel Separation: Left (Block Config) vs Right (Field Layout)

## Clear Separation

### LEFT PANEL (LeftSettingsPanel)
- **Purpose:** Block config – configures the Record List / block itself (Airtable-style sidebar)
- **Shows when:** `selectedContext` is `page`, `block`, or `recordList` + edit mode
- **Layout:** Flex sibling – interface **shrinks** when open
- **Controls:** Data (table, view, filter, sort, group), List item/card, User controls
- **Must NOT:** Field editability at schema level, record layout builder

### RIGHT PANEL (RightSettingsPanel)
- **Purpose:** Field layout editor (drag & drop) – edits `field_layout` only
- **Shows when:** Record layout context (RecordPanel edit or record_view page with record) + edit mode
- **Layout:** Absolute overlay – main content stays full width
- **Controls:** All fields, drag & drop ordering, sections, columns, hide/show
- **Must NOT:** Dataset, sort, filter, group, permissions

## Behavior Rules

**Edit Mode ON:**
- Left panel: block config (interface shrinks)
- Right panel: field layout (overlays)
- No scroll duplication, no layout jumping

**Edit Mode OFF:**
- Interface full width
- No panels visible
- No ghost shrink, no leftover padding, no persistent flex gap
